<title>USA: Anacomp sees more demand for leases.</title>
<headline>Anacomp sees more demand for leases.</headline>
<dateline>SAN DIEGO 1997-07-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>Anacomp Inc said Thursday that more customers are seeking leases or usage plans instead of straight sales of COM systems.</p>
<p>The information delivery systems and services company said that while this puts short-term pressure on revenues, it provides predictable recurring revenue streams for the future.</p>
<p>Anacomp reported a loss for the third quarter ended June 30 of $1.08 a share before a charge for early extinguishment of debt. A year earlier it reported a loss of $1.06 a share before a gain on the early extinguishment of debt.</p>
